race.comment: MR ZEUS (4) showed sharp tactical speed first-up before fitness gave out late. On the quick back-up and drawn to advantage, he should prove tougher to reel in with that run under the belt. CHUR NIBBLE (1) didn't quite meet market expectations in his Australian debut but still ran well into third. Sure to have tightened up and is backing up quickly, he's worth following. PRINCE LUCIFER (6) has built steadily this prep and looks ready to peak. Drops back to the mile and is right among the key hopes. STAGETIME (10) improved sharply third-up when chasing into fourth at Bordertown. Open to further progression and keeps Milnes aboard. MATINO (3) produced a much better effort at Clare last start and has been kept fresh with 38 days between runs. Back to the mile, he's not to be overlooked.
